                </p>
                <hr style="border: solid 1px black; max-width: 300px">
                <p class="body-content" style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 30px">8.1 E-News always respects and protects children's personal data. In addition to the personal data protection measures prescribed by law, before processing children's personal data, E-News will verify the age of the child and request the consent of (i) the child and/or (ii) the child's parents or guardians as prescribed by law.y</p>
                <hr style="border: solid 1px black; max-width: 300px">
                                <p class="body-content" style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 30px">8.2 In addition to complying with other relevant legal provisions, for the processing of personal data related to the personal data of a person declared missing/deceased, E-News will have to obtain the consent of one of the relevant persons as prescribed by current law.</p>
                <hr style="border: solid 1px black; max-width: 300px">
                <p class="body-content" style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 30px">9. Rights and obligations of users related to personal data provided to E-News</p>
                <hr style="border: solid 1px black; max-width: 300px">
                <p class="body-content" style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 30px">9.1. Users have the right to know about the processing of their personal data, unless otherwise provided by law.</p>
